<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="10" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="9.[189,457,737,763]" box="[189,457,737,763]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,457,737,763]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,457,737,763]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Differential diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[189,1399,784,881]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
Species with face medially black, yellow laterally, scutum and scutellum black, and abdomen black with lateral small yellow maculae on terga 1–5. Easy to distinguish from other species of 
<taxonomicName box="[1190,1317,819,845]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Allograpta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1190,1317,819,845]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Allograpta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the general dark coloration.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="10" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="9.[189,324,928,954]" box="[189,324,928,954]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,324,928,954]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,324,928,954]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Etymology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[189,1399,974,1036]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">The specific epithet refers to the family name of the first collector of the species, Fred Jacq, a great naturalist and photographer. The species epithet is to be treated as a noun in the genitive case.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
